## Setup Instructions

### Prerequisites

- Node.js v18 or above (v20 LTS recommended)
- npm (comes with Node.js)
- SQLite command-line tools or GUI for database inspection
- Chocolatey for Windows to install sqlite3 CLI

### Backend Setup

```
cd backend
npm install

```

Create a `.env` file in `backend/`:

PORT=5000
JWT_SECRET=your_very_secret_key
JWT_EXPIRE=7d
NODE_ENV=development


Start backend server:

```
npm run dev
```


### Frontend Setup

Open a new terminal/window:


```
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```



### Tailwind CSS Setup (Optional)

In the `frontend` directory, install and initialize Tailwind CSS:

```
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p
```



Update `tailwind.config.js` content paths and import Tailwind directives in CSS per the project guide.

---

## Usage

- Register users and log in to receive JWT tokens
- Normal users can manage their own tasks
- To make a user admin, update the role in the database (via SQLite CLI or GUI):

```
UPDATE users SET role = 'admin' WHERE email = 'admin@gmail.com';

```



Then log out and login again for role changes to take effect.

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint            | Access      | Description                          |
|--------|---------------------|-------------|------------------------------------|
| POST   | /api/auth/register  | Public      | Register user                      |
| POST   | /api/auth/login     | Public      | User login                        |
| GET    | /api/auth/me        | Auth        | Get current user info              |
| GET    | /api/tasks          | Auth        | Admin: all tasks, User: own tasks  |
| GET    | /api/tasks/:id      | Auth        | Get single task                    |
| POST   | /api/tasks          | Auth        | Create new task                   |
| PUT    | /api/tasks/:id      | Auth        | Update task                     |
| DELETE | /api/tasks/:id      | Auth        | Delete task                     |

---

## Security

- Passwords hashed with bcryptjs
- JWT tokens for stateless authentication
- Role-based access enforced backend & frontend
- Input validation with Joi
- Parameterized SQL queries to prevent SQL Injection

---

## Technologies Used

- Node.js, Express.js, SQLite3
- React (with Vite), React Router, Axios
- bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken, cors, dotenv, joi
- Tailwind CSS
